{{Infobox Journal | title = Quaerendo | cover = | editor = Lisa Kuitert | discipline = [[History of books|History of manuscripts and books]] | abbreviation = Quaerendo | publisher = [[Brill Publishers]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1971-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.brill.nl/qua | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 859945963 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0014-9527 | eISSN = 1570-0690 }} '''''Quaerendo''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] devoted to manuscripts and printed books in Europe, with a focus on the [[Low Countries]]. It was established in 1971 and covers [[codicology]], [[palaeography]], and various aspects of the [[history of books]] from around 1500 until the present. In addition to full articles, each issue contains a section dedicated to the announcement of new discoveries, publications, and recent events. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Lisa Kuitert ([[University of Amsterdam]]).
