{{For|the actress known as Rasika|Sangeetha Krish}}
{{Refimprove|date=July 2013}}
A '''rasika''' is a term for an [[aesthete]] of [[Hindustani classical music]].<ref name="Martínez2001">{{cite book|author=José Luiz Martínez|title=Semiosis in Hindustani Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OwJRnFIcM4cC&pg=PA166|accessdate=14 July 2013|date=1 January 2001|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publ.|isbn=978-81-208-1801-9|pages=166–}}</ref> The term is derived from [[Sanskrit]] meaning full of Passion, elegant; with discrimination. Connoisseur - An expert able to appreciate a field; especially in the fine arts.

A '''rasika''' is a term for audience in Sinhalese

== In the context of carnatic music ==
A '''rasika''', in [[carnatic music]] terminology, is a person who has some knowledge of carnatic music and is able to appreciate carnatic music. In carnatic music concerts (or [[katcheri]], as they are called), the audience is usually called rasikas.<ref name="Srikantiah">{{cite book|author=Jyotsna Srikanth, Rathna Srikantiah|title=Carnatic Music Learning Series - Volume 1, English|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=q0gTgJ7EfoIC&pg=PT58|accessdate=14 July 2013|publisher=Carnatic Music - English|pages=58–|id=GGKEY:20L2WJTSC5R}}</ref>

