{{Use British English|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox book| | name = The Tale of Kitty-in-Boots | image = | caption = | author = [[Beatrix Potter]] | illustrator = [[Quentin Blake]] | country = United Kingdom | language = English | genre = [[Children's literature]] | publisher = [[Frederick Warne & Co]] | release_date = September [[2016 in literature|2016]] | pages = 72<ref name=amazon /> | media_type = | oclc = }}
'''''The Tale of Kitty-in-Boots''''' is a British [[children's book]] written by [[Beatrix Potter]] and illustrated by [[Quentin Blake]] published in 2016. The manuscript was discovered by [[Jo Hanks]], a publisher at [[Penguin Random House Children's Books]], in the [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] archive in 2015. <ref name="kitty in boots">{{cite news|title=Beatrix Potter story Kitty-in-Boots discovered after 100 years|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35407846|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=26 January 2016|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref>
Potter sent the manuscript to her publisher in 1914, and mentioned in letters that she intended to complete it; however, her work was interrupted by the outbreak of [[World War I]] and personal events such as her marriage and illness.<ref name="kitty in boots"/>
The story centres around "a well-behaved prime black Kitty cat, who leads rather a double life", and includes characters from other Potter stories, including [[Peter Rabbit]], and [[Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle]].<ref name="CNN">{{Cite web|title = Lost Beatrix Potter tale 'Kitty-in-Boots' rediscovered - CNN.com|url = http://www.cnn.com/2016/01/26/entertainment/new-beatrix-potter-kitty-in-boots/index.html|website = CNN|access-date = 27 January 2016}}</ref>
The book was published on 1 September 2016 ({{ISBN|978-0241247594}}) by [[Frederick Warne & Co]], the publisher of Potter's other works, which since 1983 has been an imprint of [[Penguin Group]].<ref name=amazon>{{cite web|title=The Tale of Kitty-in-Boots|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/The-Tale-Kitty-In-Boots-Beatrix-Potter/dp/0241247594|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Frederick Warne|url=http://www.penguin.com/meet/publishers/frederickwarne/|publisher=Penguin Group|accessdate=26 January 2016}}</ref> The publication coincided with the 150th anniversary of Potter's birth.<ref name="CNN"/>
